"{\n  \"diabetes_mellitus\": {\n    \"Children_and_Adolescents\": {\n      \"description\": \"This patient population focuses on individuals diagnosed with diabetes, typically type 1 or type 2, from infancy through adolescence, requiring specialized management strategies considering growth and development.\"\n    },\n    \"Pregnant_Women\": {\n      \"description\": \"This category includes women with pre-existing diabetes (type 1 or type 2) or gestational diabetes, requiring careful monitoring and management to ensure maternal and fetal health.\"\n    },\n    \"Elderly_Individuals\": {\n      \"description\": \"This subcategory encompasses older adults (typically 65 years and older) with diabetes, who often present with multiple comorbidities and age-related physiological changes impacting diabetes management.\"\n    },\n    \"Patients_with_Cardiovascular_Disease\": {\n      \"description\": \"This group comprises individuals with diabetes who also have pre-existing or concurrent cardiovascular conditions, such as coronary artery disease or heart failure, necessitating integrated treatment approaches.\"\n    },\n    \"Individuals_with_Chronic_Kidney_Disease\": {\n      \"description\": \"This patient population includes those with diabetes and chronic kidney disease, a common and progressive complication requiring tailored management to slow disease progression and prevent adverse outcomes.\"\n    }\n  }\n}"